From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PiTv Build <build@pitv>
Date: Wed, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ECMQmlModule6: drop QT_NO_CREATE_VERSIONLESS_FUNCTIONS guard

ECMQmlModule6.cmake sets QT_NO_CREATE_VERSIONLESS_FUNCTIONS=ON before
calling find_package(Qt6 COMPONENTS Core Qml) to avoid registering Qt
versionless function aliases during ECM's own module initialisation.

In a cross-compilation Yocto build, the Qml plugin dependency chain
(via Qt6quick3dspatialaudioplugin → Qt6Quick3D → Qt6ShaderTools, and
via other plugins → Qt6DBus etc.) causes those Qt module config files
to be loaded for the first time while the flag is set.  Because cmake
marks these packages as "already found" after the first load, subsequent
find_package calls for Qt6ShaderTools, Qt6DBus, etc. in downstream
CMakeLists.txt are no-ops — their config files are never re-included,
so the versionless aliases (qt_add_shaders, qt_add_dbus_interface, ...)
are never registered.  The build then fails with
  "Unknown CMake command qt_add_shaders / qt_add_dbus_interface / ..."

The guard is not necessary for correctness: projects that include
ECMQmlModule already depend on Qt6 Qml, and having the standard Qt
versionless aliases defined is both expected and harmless.  Remove the
two lines that set and unset the flag.

Upstream-Status: Pending
---
 modules/ECMQmlModule6.cmake | 2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/modules/ECMQmlModule6.cmake b/modules/ECMQmlModule6.cmake
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/modules/ECMQmlModule6.cmake
+++ b/modules/ECMQmlModule6.cmake
@@ -7,9 +7,7 @@

 cmake_policy(VERSION 3.16)

-set(QT_NO_CREATE_VERSIONLESS_FUNCTIONS ON)
 find_package(Qt6 COMPONENTS Core Qml CONFIG)
-unset(QT_NO_CREATE_VERSIONLESS_FUNCTIONS)

 if (NOT TARGET Qt6::Qml)
     message(WARNING "Target Qt6::Qml was not found. ECMQmlModule requires the QML module when building with Qt 6")
